<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="76" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
The new species is known from the type locality only. The Chirinda Forest is an isolated patch of mountain forest on Mt. Selinda from about 1000 m to 1250 m elevation in East Zimbabwe (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 9. Map of southern Africa showing the type locality of V. chirindensis sp. n. in Zimbabwe (20 ° 24 ' S 32 ° 41 ' E)." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.65.23538.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/191730" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">9</figureCitation>
). The species may occur also in the Chimanimani Mts. north of the Chirinda Forest.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="76" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="1" pageNumber="76">
<bibRefCitation author="Janse, AJT" journalOrPublisher="The Moths of South Africa" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 136" refId="B8" refString="Janse, AJT, 1964. Limacodidae. The Moths of South Africa 7: 1 - 136" title="Limacodidae." volume="7" year="1964">Janse (1964)</bibRefCitation>
was not able to examine himself all species known at that time. But he included the information provided by other authors in his revisionary work (e.g. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933708655316" author="West, RJ" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" refId="B19" refString="West, RJ, 1937. Descriptions of new species of Limacodidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (10)20: 77-87. https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933708655316" title="Descriptions of new species of Limacodidae. Annals and Magazine of Natural History (10) 20: 77 - 87." url="https://doi.org/10.1080/00222933708655316" year="1937">West 1937</bibRefCitation>
). In addition, after 1964 a number of further species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1845" class="Hexapoda" family="Limacodidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Limacodidae</taxonomicName>
was described from Africa (
<bibRefCitation author="Carcasson, RH" journalOrPublisher="Journal of the East African Natural History Society" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" pagination="131 - 160" refId="B2" refString="Carcasson, RH, 1965. New Lepidoptera from East Africa. Journal of the East African Natural History Society 25 (2): 131 - 160" title="New Lepidoptera from East Africa." volume="25" year="1965">Carcasson 1965</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Pinhey, ECG" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Transvaal Museum" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" pagination="153 - 176" refId="B13" refString="Pinhey, ECG, 1968. Some new African Lepidoptera. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 25 (9): 153 - 176" title="Some new African Lepidoptera." volume="25" year="1968">Pinhey 1968</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Rougeot, PC" journalOrPublisher="Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (A)" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 150" refId="B15" refString="Rougeot, PC, 1977. Lepidoptera. Missions entomologiques en Ethiopie 1973-1975. Fascicule 1. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle (A) 105: 1 - 150" title="Lepidoptera. Missions entomologiques en Ethiopie 1973 - 1975. Fascicule 1." volume="105" year="1977">Rougeot 1977</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viette, P" journalOrPublisher="Faune de Madagascar" pageId="3" pageNumber="78" pagination="1 - 162" refId="B18" refString="Viette, P, 1980. Insects Lepidopteres Limacodidae. Faune de Madagascar 53: 1 - 162" title="Insects Lepidopteres Limacodidae." volume="53" year="1980">Viette 1980</bibRefCitation>
). They are fully scaled and not related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Mey, 2018" authorityName="Mey" authorityYear="2018" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Vansoniella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Vansoniella" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Vansoniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. n., with the exception of males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hering" baseAuthorityYear="1957" class="Insecta" family="Limacodidae" genus="Latoia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Latoia pumilus" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pumilus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">Latoia pumilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Hering, 1957) and 
<taxonomicName genus="L." lsidName="L. heringi" pageId="1" pageNumber="76" rank="species" species="heringi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="76">L. heringi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Viette, 1965) from Madagascar which exhibit some resemblance by the presence of hyaline patches on the forewings, but other characters as antennal structure and wing venation indicate that this resemblance is due to convergence.
</paragraph>
